wwpIpInterfaceMIB.name: wwpIpInterfaceMIB

revisions.description: A new object for mgmt packet priority is added.

wwpIpInterfaceMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpIpInterfaceMIB.description: The MIB module for the WWP IpInterface Ip interfaces config. This MIB provide additional configuration to whatever is provided by the standard ip group.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpIpInterfaceTable.name: wwpIpInterfaceTable
wwpIpInterfaceTable.description: Table of IP addresses and associated subnet mask.

wwpIpInterfaceEntry.name: wwpIpInterfaceEntry
wwpIpInterfaceEntry.description: Interface IP and subnet mask entry. These interfaces are used to cause the switch CPU to become involved witht he IP traffic. By default, a minimum of two interfaces must always exist, one for the local mgt interface, one for the remote mgt interface, and one or more for voice over IP.

wwpIpInterfaceName.name: wwpIpInterfaceName
wwpIpInterfaceName.description: The friendly name for the IP interface.

wwpIpInterfaceIpAddr.name: wwpIpInterfaceIpAddr
wwpIpInterfaceIpAddr.description: IP address associated with this interface.

wwpIpInterfaceSubnet.name: wwpIpInterfaceSubnet
wwpIpInterfaceSubnet.description: The subnet mask associated with this ip address/interface.

wwpIpInterfaceIfIndexXref.name: wwpIpInterfaceIfIndexXref
wwpIpInterfaceIfIndexXref.description: Cross reference to MIB-2 Interfaces ifIndex.

wwpIpExtInterfaceTable.name: wwpIpExtInterfaceTable
wwpIpExtInterfaceTable.description: A table that contains Interface Specific information maintained by each interface.

wwpIpExtInterfaceEntry.name: wwpIpExtInterfaceEntry
wwpIpExtInterfaceEntry.description: A list of interfaces additional config parameters maintained by each interface.

wwpIpInterfaceEnable.name: wwpIpInterfaceEnable
wwpIpInterfaceEnable.description: The status of each interface. A value of true(1) indicates that this interface is enabled and a value of false(2) indicates that this interface is disabled. The device shouldn't allow the Management Station to disable all the interfaces available on the box.

wwpIpInterfaceVlanId.name: wwpIpInterfaceVlanId
wwpIpInterfaceVlanId.description: The vlanId associated with this IP interface. The vlan indicated by wwpIpInterfaceVlanId should exist in the Vlan Table. If an interface has no vlan assocaited, then any read on this object should return 'noSuchInstance'.

wwpIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority.name: wwpIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority
wwpIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority.description: The 802.1p Priority value for the mgmt traffic on this interface.

wwpIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled.name: wwpIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled
wwpIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification.name: wwpIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification
wwpIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification.description: A wwpIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification is sent whenever the ip address of an interface changes.
